30/09/2003
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- Croatia and Hungary signed a bilateral agreement on border traffic control Monday (29 September), during Croatian President Stipe Mesic's visit to Budapest.
Afterwards, at a joint news conference with Mesic, Hungarian President Ferenz Madl said the accords would enable the interstate border to remain open after Hungary joins the EU next May.
Madl also expressed his country's support for Croatia's efforts to join NATO and the EU.
(MTI - 30/09/03;
HINA, BBC - 29/09/03)
